chapter:
&reftitle.setup;




 &reftitle.required;


   This extension depends on log4cxx library.
   On Unix-like systems you need to download the lib source from Log4cxx Repository
   and follow this installation instructions.




   Windows users just need to download the pre-compiled extension from php_logger-win32,
   extract the log4cxx.dll into the php dir, and the php_logger.dll into the ext dir.







 &reftitle.install;


   To compile the extension on unix-like systems, you just need to add --with-logger[log4cxx install dir].
   If you compile as a shared module then add extension="php_logger.so" to you php.ini file.



   On windows just add the extension="php_logger.dll" to your php.ini file.








 &reftitle.runtime;


   The framework loades its configuration from log4j.properties file.



   For examples and information about how to write a log4j.properties file
   please refer to log4cxx site.








 &reftitle.resources;
 &no.resource;
